{
  "stem": "13690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had a built-in tabernacle in the house, which is being called the sukkah.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we even have guests in our home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say, most of the-- most of the time, I would say Polish, but as well, Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I attend cheder at the early age of four, five.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then, of course, public school, which was quite obligatory to attend.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I do-- I did experience some kind of uneasiness, but I would say that it was not that the children did understand what means 'anti-Semitism.' If they came with a certain hatred or discomfort, it was only because probably, or most likely, they were-- they were taught at home, or being told at home.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Same thing goes on our behalf.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Coming from a Jewish home, I don't think so that I was free to associate with the Gentile children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the same, probably-- the Gentile children could not associate with the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I do remember vividly one incident, which was a very tragic one.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was in a summer month where school-- the public school-- was closed, and I attended cheder, which is the Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the town arrived, in the marketplace, or to say, the center of the town-- a bus arrived.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In those days, a bus-- it was for me, as a child, a novice, to run to the bus and see it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, it's a bus, luxurious bus.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't even had an opportunity to run closely to the bus, whereby 30 or 40 young men jumped out of the bus, just destroying Jewish property.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Just practically beating up Jewish people, which was a very unusual thing for me and will always remember in my memory.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was told later on that this was an organization.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
